Package gov.ca.water.calgui.presentation

In this package we have the we have the presentation class for the whole application.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Report.PlotType  
    Report.Writer
    Externalizes the format for output.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CalLiteInitClass
    This class is for initializing the Application and adding the Action, Item, and Mouse Listeners to the main frame.
    ControlFrame
    Floating frame to display Quick Result scenario and display control panels
    DisplayFrame
    DisplayFrame class provides a frame for showing charts.
    GlobalActionListener
    This class is for Listening all the action events(Button click) which are generated by the application.
    GlobalChangeListener
    This class is for Listening all the change events which are generated by the application.(We only use this for "Regulations" tab)
    GlobalItemListener
    This class is for Listening all the item events(radio button, check box) which are generated by the application.
    GlobalMouseListener
    This class is for Listening all the mouse events which are generated by the application.
    PowerFrame  
    ProgressFrame
    This frame is used for displaying updated status during long-duration activities like saving scenarios and running CalLite.
    ProgressFrameForPDF
    This frame is used for displaying the monitored status of run and save operations.
    Report
    Generates a report based on the template file instructions
    Report.PathnameMap  
    ScenarioFrame
    This frame is used for the "View Scenario Settings" button in the "Run Settings" tab.
    SchematicMain
    SchematicMain: Class to handle display of SVG-formatted schematic view.
    WRIMSGUILinks
    Methods for updating Project values in the WRIMS GUI object space from CalLite GUI
